{"word":"Λακεδαίμων","slug":"Λακεδαίμων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Λακεδαίμων</b></el> <el>(Λᾰκεδαίμων, ονος,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>Lacedaemon</i>, the capital of Laconia, and <i>Laconia</i> itself, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; but <a href='S:regular, regularly'>regul.</a> <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <el>Λακεδαιμόνιος, α, ον</el>, of persons, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}